SIMPLE: adipose
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adipose
<hw>Ad"i*pose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>The fat present in the cells of adipose tissue, composed mainly of
varying mixtures of tripalmitin, tristearin, and triolein. It solidifies
after death.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adipose</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Adipose
<hw>Ad"i*pose`</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>adeps</ets>, <ets>adipis</ets>, fat, grease.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to animal fat; fatty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Adipose fin</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a soft
boneless fin.</cd> -- <col><b>Adipose tissue</b></col>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>that form of animal tissue which forms or
contains fat.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adiposity</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Adiposeness</ent>⟦br⟧
